I feel lucky to have been able to experience in just a few days the bountiful of Colombia 🇨🇴 and his outstanding gastronomy. Most of them highlighting the produce of the Amazon and northern indigenous communities. With a unique voice hardly found anywhere else. Now South America doesn’t have to keep looking North but only to our beautiful continent to be so proud of.
Forever grateful to @leorestaurantcol from Leonor Espinosa from bringing such a platform to the native communities of Colombia and for the wonderful hospitality of @alvclv Alvaro Clavijo, @humonegro_bog, @prudencia_restaurante 🧡🇨🇴

Our spaghetti squash pavlova is back tomorrow @thefrenchroom_ 💝

This dessert was at the opening menu at Mena last year and it was such a hit! - inspired by a fruit called Alcayota in Chile 🇨🇱 - we cook the squash in a syrup with vanilla and star anise. The alcayota in Chile is not a squash but you have to also steam or boil to shred all the flesh. Our winter pavlova goes with passion fruit, fingerlime and a citrus curd. Refreshing, sweet and tangy… hitting all the spots!

Thank you @bg_reinhart @d_magazine for this surprising glowing review. 
It is true that while I may have had my share of residencies it’s hard to know what to expect, especially whether people really care about the work being done behind the scenes and what the guest chef is trying to bring to the table at a new space.
It’s been a great ride, with incredible individuals and wonderful support. I’m glad that the work being done here is recognized and that I was able to bring a little bit of me and Mena to Dallas, TX. 
We have only 4 weeks to go and I’m very grateful for this review and for this really fun and unique opportunity @thefrenchroom_ 🤠💪🏽🇨🇱🥰

“Every good friend was once a stranger” - this is the last day of the residency here in TX, Dallas. I can’t say I’m not happy to be going to my second home, NY. But I also know that this residency has touched me in more ways than any other. I came here with an open heart and open mind and to be open to an experience I had no expectations of. It has been the most special and close to my heart. The connections I’ve made here will stay with me forever and I can tell you one thing, I’ll be coming back to visit! 
To say hi to the people that have gone on this crazy ride with me and that have grown and learn just like me. 
To lessons learn, to BBQ! To all these connections that were so obvious … to all the people that cared and pushed and laughed with me. I’m sad but … Dallas, you are only 2,5 hr away!

Thank you for filling my heart when home away from home 🫶🏽❤️💕

Mark your calendars! April 30th! 
Super excited to be part of the Kelp dinner in celebration of the New England Kelp harvest week. In collaboration with @shipwrightsdaughter 
We will create a menu based on one of my favorite ingredients- Seaweed! to celebrate the end of harvest. Don’t miss it! Come and enjoy the beauty of Mystic, CT! 💕

I can’t believe that only a few weeks ago I was in Chile, specifically in Topocalma, 2.5 hours away from Santiago. Meeting the wonderful seaweed harvester, Pamela and the wonderful Juan Butazzonni from @fundacionrompientes
The wild seaweed harvesting in this area runs from November - April. In a beautiful area of 3000 hectares protected by the government thanks to @fundacionrompientes … i’m not only proud to have met them but also humble to be working together to bring a better source of income to the people collecting seaweed and help create a sense of belonging in the country. So much more to discover and learn from this beautiful land ❤️ I call home.

#seaweed #cochayuyo # luche #luga #fundacionrompientes #chile #topocalma

Tonight’s the night!! @shipwrightsdaughter Kelp dinner celebrating the end kelp harvest season. Lucky me to have seen such different seaweed environments in the last month. This beautiful cultivated sugar kelp from Mystic, CT from @stoningtonkelpco will be showcased all over our menu tonight. 
So happy to learn we are sold out!!! - I bet you didn’t know that kelp could be so cool 😂😎

Industry night series 3 presented by @sanpellegrino_us continues this month with Chef @victoriablamey 

Her cuisine is characterized by her use of fresh, seasonal ingredients and her willingness to experiment with new flavors and techniques. Known the world over for electrifying menus wherever she goes, and adding a dose of environmental consciousness.

Dubbed by New York Times food critic, Pete Wells as “A chef worth following” Blamey has worked at Michelin star restaurants all over the world and gained further recognition as the executive chef of Mena in 2022 and Gotham Bar and Grill, where she received three stars from the New York Times.

Eric Tran and Victoria Blamey are bringing the Asian and Latin flavors of their families together to bring you an industry night to remember. 

Our 6 course dac biet dinner ($88pp) will feature veggies from one of our favorite farms @norwichmeadowsfarm and highlighting sea treasures of the Atlantic. 

@luvl1sa will be on the 1’s and 2’s. 
You will not want to miss this party! Bookings are live on @resy

On a date like this, on a July 9th (2022) Mena closed it doors. 
It’s so bizarre to think that a year has passed. 
I can’t say that it was just a “difficult” moment because the grief and loss was felt much later. I still believe that Mena will come at one point but I want to make sure it will come back to stay and be the mothership.
Today, a year later, even though it’s sad to think about it, I’m also very hopeful. Hopeful that I will continue to do the craft I love and hopeful that we make those better times around us. I was very lucky to have bene through this period of time with the people that made Mena what is was, even if for a short period of time. Lucky and grateful for the love I received during that time and the unconditional support from love ones that were unconditionally by my side. I don’t think you ever get over something or someone that you have loved deeply, but I do think that’s a positive place to be. People and situations shape us to take a hard look at ourselves, our lives and our actions. That may not be an easy task, but I’ve also realized that Im a hopeful person for life. And hope it’s the last thing we can lose.
Fun challenges, but challenges none the less are coming my way and I can’t wait to share them with you, soon enough 💕
Respect grief and loss, respect change and acceptance of who you really are and want you want to be.

When Euro Vic shows up… there’s no haters around.

I feel very lucky to have experience and amazing week in Norway with @seafoodfromnorway_us and and incredible, very well put together group to share this experience with. Not only this trip was fun, beautiful and exciting but so educational for me and the rest of the group. We learnt about farmed fish, specifically Atlantic Salmon, the myths, the misinformation, the pros, the challenges, the solutions and the questions that have yet no conclusive answers.
It has changed my perspective in an 180 way. I tell you why; the transparency I have experienced from not only one but several farms that we visit. The open book to show the whole process from start to finish, including a salmon processing facility which is so fundamental to the whole organization. Thank you to @seafoodfromnorway_us for this incredible week, @anneoeen for her amazing self and knowledge, @yoniyums for the wonderful spirit and so ready with his blue suitcase of emergency items such as candy (that he ended up eating by himself 🤫😊😘) and the whole group for their disposition to participate, share and be kind to one another which exactly what the world needs right now.

I bet you guys didn’t know that I have done vegan dishes for the past 6 years?! Honestly, without the intention of doing plant based I have been around it for a long time. 
Now @publicrecordsnyc you guys get the chance to see a full vegan menu for two days! October 26-27! - I have loved @publicrecordsnyc since the beginning. Not only it’s a great place to enjoy amazing music artists and collaborations but also since its conception it has been a vegan only venue. Francis Harris @francisscissor and his partners have created an amazing community @publicrecordsnyc and that’s why I’m so thrilled to finally been able to lock in a couple of days to do this event. Do not miss it!! There won’t be another chance. You’ll see it’s gonna be a busy November and an even more exciting December once the cat is out the bag 😉
Two nights!! This October 26 & 27! Till lights go out! Great music by @francisscissor and pairings to go with this fun event plus…There’s always dancing in the music room if you feel like it. I know I will 😊

Since I’ve been so quiet apparently … 🤫 some news for you all 🫠

I’m not the one to recap my year on a post, only internally. But this year has been painful, intense and felt like many years and lives lived.
I am grateful for being strong in moments that I thought I couldn’t, grateful to have a lot of love in my heart.  I’m thankful for the gorgeous and supportive mother that I have who reminds me I’m not alone. Thankful for the old friends that try to understand me and be by my side. Thankful for the new friends I’m able to make even when we think that it’s more and more difficult as we grow older.
I’m on a journey to understand myself and the people around me, to see how to live a more balanced life and be fulfilled. On a journey to keep loving and living intensely but making better decisions that take care of myself and the people I love and surround myself with people that make me grow and that want my love back.
This year has been painful for humanity and we seem to keep inflicting pain on each other. Hope is the last thing to lose, I definitely have endless hope. 
To another year trying to find the balance we need, to another year always trying even if it means falling down over and over. To never stop trying to be brave and take on new or old challenges and keep loving, loving fully.

#hereto2024
